bug.short_desc: Copy and creative concepts - Juniper global airport ad campaign

long_desc.thetext:
> Some context
Juniper Networks launched its global airport campaign in Fall 2009 and have featured customers like NYSE, Tesla, Priceline, SingTel, NOAA...
In 2011, Juniper's investment will surpass $20M, Twitter will be a featured client.
They would like to add Mozilla to their featured customer list, ASAP – media is currently being purchased worldwide and Mozilla could be posted as early as mid-May.
> What we need to do We need to provide some guidance (copy and general creative directions) to tweak the current creative they submitted. Constraint: the theme of Juniper's campaign is "It's time" so the headline will have to incorporate this.
> Current creative See attached presentation (previous creative on slide 10, current creative on slide 11 & 12).
> Our feedback so far - The community angle is nice but lacks purpose (what is the common goal?). We would prefer talk about the better web ("It's time for a better web" / "It's time to build a better web") - The population number is off. It is good to incorporate the idea of a large community and the numbers will matter to Juniper as it adds credibility to their security/reliability message. I would suggest using the official number for now (450,000,000) and tie it more closely to the mission. - The creative is great but has too much of a Southern European feel. They will need to find something more universal than this. - Needs a bigger logo
Matej, could you work on the copy (headlines and paragraph) and also help us find a visual concept for the main visual? We need something that expresses the idea of building a better web, ideally in a community setting.
Let me know if you would like to discuss / brainstorm.
Hey Greg - sounds great. The deck you attached only has slides up to 9. Did you have a different deck with slides 11 & 12?
Sorry about this. The presentation was too heavy to upload so I had to kill a few slides. Just focus on 8-9, they are the previous 11-12.

Here are some alternate lines I've come up with so far. I'm also adding Martell to the bug, just in case he has some thoughts about visual direction (he already suggested big, 3D letters coming out of a crowd of people for the community-themed lines). Let me know if you like any of these or if I should keep going:
It’s time for a browser that answers to no one but you. All 450,000,000 of you.
It’s time to put the Web back in the hands of the users. (450,000,000 of them, to be exact.)
It’s time for more people to do more on the Web. (450,000,000, to be exact.)
It’s time for the Web to make a difference in 450,000,000 lives.
It’s time for 450,000,000 people to stand up for the Web.
It’s time to make the Web a better place.
It's time for a browser that's made to make the Web a better place.
It’s time to keep the Web free, open, accessible and awesome.
It’s time for the Web to change the world.
It’s time to put users back in control of the Web.
It’s time for a browser that answers to no one but you.
It’s time for a browser that places principles over profit.

Not a huge fan of "to be exact", I vote for: It’s time for a browser that answers to no one but you. It’s time to make the Web a better place. It’s time for a browser that answers to no one but you. All 450,000,000 of you. It's time for a browser that's made to make the Web a better place.
